== Events == * [[Emperor Yūryaku]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[456]] [[December 25]]) – In the 1st year of Emperor Yūryaku, the 21st Emperor Yūryaku acceded to the throne. * [[Genroku]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1695]] [[December 18]]) – In accordance with the Edict on Compassion for Living Beings, a doghouse covering 160,000 tsubo was constructed in Musashi-Nakano Village to shelter stray dogs. * [[黄帝紀元]] 4609th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1912]] [[January 1]]) – In the Republic of China, the calendar was reformed from the lunisolar to the Gregorian system and the Minguo era began.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1537]] [[December 15]]) – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, the 15th Shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (d. [[1597]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1563]] [[November 28]]) – Hosokawa Tadaoki, military commander ({{ill|Busho (rank)|ja|Military Commander|12=draft}}) and Daimyo; the first lord of the Ogura Domain (d. [[1646]] {{Sfn|永尾|p=178}}). * {{ill|Meireki|ja|Meireki|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1656]] [[December 28]]) – Azumi Tanpaku, Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|Confucian Scholar|zh|儒生|12=draft}}) (d. [[1738]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[December 24]]) – Yamashita Yoshitaro ({{ill|Yamashita Yoshitaro|ja|山下芳太郎|12=draft}}), founder of Kanamojikai ({{ill|Kanamojikai|ja|カナモジカイ|12=draft}}) (d. [[1923]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1574]] [[November 26]]) – Kobayakawa Shigehira, Sengoku daimyo (born [[1542]]). * [[Kangxi]] 61st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1722]] [[December 20]]) – Kangxi Emperor,<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Kangxi Kangxi emperor of Qing dynasty] {{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|ja|Encyclopædia Britannica|12=draft}}</ref> the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (born [[1654]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|Genji|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1864]] [[December 11]]) – Fukuhara Motomasa (also known as Fukuhara Echigo), chief retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born [[1815]]).
== Commemorations ==
