qq-November 13 (Lunisolar)-qq {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11th Month (Old Calendar)|1=November (Lunisolar)|2=ja|3=11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyo|ja|Rokuyo|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|Taian|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[Emperor Yūryaku]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[456]] [[December 25]]) – In the 1st year of Emperor Yūryaku, the 21st Emperor Yūryaku acceded to the throne. * [[Genroku]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1695]] [[December 18]]) – In accordance with the Edict on Compassion for Living Beings, a doghouse covering 160,000 tsubo was constructed in Musashi-Nakano Village to shelter stray dogs. * {{ill|Huangdi Era|ja|黄帝紀元|nl|Chinese_jaartelling|zh-min-nan|Hông-tè_kì-goân|zh-classical|黃帝紀元|zh|黄帝纪元|qq=}} 4609th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1912]] [[January 1]]) – In the Republic of China, the calendar was reformed from the lunisolar to the Gregorian system and the Minguo era began.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1537]] [[December 15]]) – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, the 15th Shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (d. [[1597]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1563]] [[November 28]]) – Hosokawa Tadaoki, military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|Military Commander|qq=}}) and Daimyo; the first lord of the Ogura Domain (d. [[1646]] {{Sfn|永尾|p=178|qq=}}). * {{ill|Meireki|ja|Meireki|qq=}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1656]] [[December 28]]) – Azumi Tanpaku, Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|Confucian Scholar|zh|儒生|qq=}}) (d. [[1738]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[December 24]]) – Yamashita Yoshitaro ({{ill|Yamashita Yoshitaro|ja|山下芳太郎|qq=}}), founder of Kanamojikai ({{ill|Kanamojikai|ja|カナモジカイ|qq=}}) (d. [[1923]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|qq=}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1574]] [[November 26]]) – Kobayakawa Shigehira, Sengoku daimyo (born [[1542]]). * [[Kangxi]] 61st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1722]] [[December 20]]) – Kangxi Emperor,<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Kangxi Kangxi emperor of Qing dynasty] {{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|ja|Encyclopædia Britannica|qq=}}</ref> the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (born [[1654]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|Genji|qq=}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1864]] [[December 11]]) – Fukuhara Motomasa (also known as Fukuhara Echigo), chief retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born [[1815]]).
