{{Not to be confused with|November 13|qq=November 13}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月十三|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 13일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11th Month (Old Calendar)|1=November (Lunisolar)|2=ja|3=11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyo|ja|Rokuyo|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyo|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|Taian|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
== Events == * [[Emperor Yūryaku]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[456]] [[December 25]]) – In the 1st year of Emperor Yūryaku, the 21st Emperor Yūryaku acceded to the throne. * [[Genroku]] 8th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1695|1695]] [[December 18]]) – In accordance with the Edict on Compassion for Living Beings, a doghouse covering 160,000 tsubo was constructed in Musashi-Nakano Village to shelter stray dogs. * {{ill|Huangdi Era|ja|黄帝紀元|nl|Chinese_jaartelling|zh-min-nan|Hông-tè_kì-goân|zh-classical|黃帝紀元|zh|黄帝纪元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Huangdi Era|qq=}} 4609th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1912]] [[January 1]]) – In the Republic of China, the calendar was reformed from the lunisolar to the Gregorian system and the Minguo era began.
== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1537|1537]] [[December 15]]) – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, the 15th Shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (d. [[:en:1597|1597]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1563|1563]] [[November 28]]) – Hosokawa Tadaoki, military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|Military Commander|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) and Daimyo; the first lord of the Ogura Domain (d. [[:en:1646|1646]] {{Sfn|永尾|p=178|qq=}}). * {{ill|Meireki|ja|Meireki|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meireki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1656|1656]] [[December 28]]) – Azumi Tanpaku, Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|Confucian Scholar|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) (d. [[:en:1738|1738]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[December 24]]) – Yamashita Yoshitaro ({{ill|Yamashita Yoshitaro|ja|山下芳太郎|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashita Yoshitaro|qq=}}), founder of Kanamojikai ({{ill|Kanamojikai|ja|カナモジカイ|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanamojikai|qq=}}) (d. [[1923]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1574|1574]] [[November 26]]) – Kobayakawa Shigehira, Sengoku daimyo (born [[:en:1542|1542]]). * [[Kangxi]] 61st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1722|1722]] [[December 20]]) – Kangxi Emperor,<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Kangxi Kangxi emperor of Qing dynasty] {{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|ja|Encyclopædia Britannica|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Encyclopædia Britannica|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ブリタニカ百科事典}}</ref> the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (born [[:en:1654|1654]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|Genji|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[December 11]]) – Fukuhara Motomasa (also known as Fukuhara Echigo), chief retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born [[:en:1815|1815]]).
