== Births == * [[Tenbun]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1537|1537]] [[December 15]]) – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, the 15th Shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (d. [[:en:1597|1597]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1563|1563]] [[November 28]]) – Hosokawa Tadaoki, military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|Military Commander|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) and Daimyo; the first lord of the Ogura Domain (d. [[:en:1646|1646]] {{Sfn|永尾|p=178|qq=}}). * {{ill|Meireki|ja|Meireki|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meireki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1656|1656]] [[December 28]]) – Azumi Tanpaku, Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|Confucian Scholar|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) (d. [[:en:1738|1738]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[December 24]]) – Yamashita Yoshitaro ({{ill|Yamashita Yoshitaro|ja|山下芳太郎|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashita Yoshitaro|qq=}}), founder of Kanamojikai ({{ill|Kanamojikai|ja|カナモジカイ|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanamojikai|qq=}}) (d. [[:en:1923|1923]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1574|1574]] [[November 26]]) – Kobayakawa Shigehira, Sengoku daimyo (born [[:en:1542|1542]]). * [[Kangxi]] 61st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1722|1722]] [[December 20]]) – Kangxi Emperor,<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Kangxi Kangxi emperor of Qing dynasty] {{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|ja|Encyclopædia Britannica|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Encyclopædia Britannica|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ブリタニカ百科事典}}</ref> the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (born [[:en:1654|1654]]). * {{ill|Genji|ja|Genji|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[December 11]]) – Fukuhara Motomasa (also known as Fukuhara Echigo), chief retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born [[:en:1815|1815]]).
