'''November 13''' is the 13th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11th Month (Old Calendar)|1=November (Lunisolar)|2=ja|3=11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyo|ja|Rokuyo|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyo|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|Taian|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Emperor Yūryaku|en|Emperor Yūryaku|WD=Q357235|lt=Emperor Yūryaku|1=Emperor Yūryaku}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|456|en|456|WD=Q30432|lt=456|1=456}} {{ill|December 25|en|December 25|WD=Q2745|lt=December 25|1=December 25}}) – In the 1st year of Emperor Yūryaku, the 21st Emperor Yūryaku acceded to the throne.
* {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|WD=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1695|en|1695|WD=Q7696|lt=1695|1=1695}} {{ill|December 18|en|December 18|WD=Q2438|lt=December 18|1=December 18}}) – In accordance with the Edict on Compassion for Living Beings, a doghouse covering 160,000 tsubo was constructed in Musashi-Nakano Village to shelter stray dogs.
* {{ill|Huangdi Era|ja|黄帝紀元|nl|Chinese_jaartelling|zh-min-nan|Hông-tè_kì-goân|zh-classical|黃帝紀元|zh|黄帝纪元|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Huangdi Era|1=Huangdi Era|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3476000}} 4609th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1912|en|1912|WD=Q2077|lt=1912|1=1912}} {{ill|January 1|en|January 1|WD=Q2150|lt=January 1|1=January 1}}) – In the Republic of China, the calendar was reformed from the lunisolar to the Gregorian system and the Minguo era began.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenbun|en|Tenbun|WD=Q1192853|lt=Tenbun|1=Tenbun}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1537|en|1537|WD=Q6461|lt=1537|1=1537}} {{ill|December 15|en|December 15|WD=Q2383|lt=December 15|1=December 15}}) – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, the 15th Shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (d. {{ill|1597|en|1597|WD=Q6790|lt=1597|1=1597}}).
* {{ill|Eiroku|en|Eiroku|WD=Q1143341|lt=Eiroku|1=Eiroku}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1563|en|1563|WD=Q6629|lt=1563|1=1563}} {{ill|November 28|en|November 28|WD=Q3017|lt=November 28|1=November 28}}) – Hosokawa Tadaoki, military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|Military Commander|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) and Daimyo; the first lord of the Ogura Domain (d. {{ill|1646|en|1646|WD=Q6930|lt=1646|1=1646}} {{Sfn|永尾|p=178|qq=}}).
* {{ill|Meireki|ja|Meireki|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meireki|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1656|en|1656|WD=Q6982|lt=1656|1=1656}} {{ill|December 28|en|December 28|WD=Q2832|lt=December 28|1=December 28}}) – Azumi Tanpaku, Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|Confucian Scholar|zh|儒生|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) (d. {{ill|1738|en|1738|WD=Q6996|lt=1738|1=1738}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1871|en|1871|WD=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} {{ill|December 24|en|December 24|WD=Q2705|lt=December 24|1=December 24}}) – Yamashita Yoshitaro ({{ill|Yamashita Yoshitaro|ja|山下芳太郎|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashita Yoshitaro|1=Yoshitarō Yamashita|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6282623}}), founder of Kanamojikai ({{ill|Kanamojikai|ja|カナモジカイ|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanamojikai|1=Kanamozikai|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11294454}}) (d. {{ill|1923|en|1923|WD=Q2169|lt=1923|1=1923}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1574|en|1574|WD=Q6680|lt=1574|1=1574}} {{ill|November 26|en|November 26|WD=Q3019|lt=November 26|1=November 26}}) – Kobayakawa Shigehira, Sengoku daimyo (born {{ill|1542|en|1542|WD=Q6520|lt=1542|1=1542}}).
* [[:en:Kangxi|Kangxi]] 61st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1722|en|1722|WD=Q6918|lt=1722|1=1722}} {{ill|December 20|en|December 20|WD=Q2455|lt=December 20|1=December 20}}) – Kangxi Emperor,<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/biography/Kangxi Kangxi emperor of Qing dynasty] {{ill|Encyclopædia Britannica|ja|Encyclopædia Britannica|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Encyclopædia Britannica|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ブリタニカ百科事典|1=Encyclopædia Britannica|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q455}}</ref> the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (born {{ill|1654|en|1654|WD=Q6970|lt=1654|1=1654}}).
* {{ill|Genji|ja|Genji|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genji|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|WD=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|December 11|en|December 11|WD=Q2363|lt=December 11|1=December 11}}) – Fukuhara Motomasa (also known as Fukuhara Echigo), chief retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born {{ill|1815|en|1815|WD=Q6948|lt=1815|1=1815}}).

